The European Union (EU) in partnership with the United Nations Childrenâ€™s Fund (UNICEF) has renovated and equipped two Primary Health Care Centres (PHCs) in Ganji and Tudun Wada communities of Warji Local Government Area of Bauchi State. The facilities were commissioned and handed over to the communities on Saturday through the Bauchi State Primary Health Care Development Agency (BASPHCDA). Speaking at the handing over ceremony at Tudun Wada village, UNICEF, Bauchi Chief of Field Office, Bhanu Pathak, said the project was part of its resolve in making health care accessible to people particularly those in the rural areas that are hard to reach. The UNICEF, Bauchi Chief of Field Office, also appealed to the state government to effectively manage the facilities. While receiving the facilities on behalf of the state government, Executive Chairman of Bauchi State Primary Health Care Development Agency (BASPHCDA), Dr. Rilwanu Mohammed, commended the EU-UNICEF collaboration for complementing the efforts of the state government in improving the health sector, adding that their intervention has really helped in improving the health sector in the state. In his remarks, Head of Administration, Warji LGA, Abubakar Ibrahim Mohammed, described the development as a good move that will ensure that healthcare delivery was brought close to the grassroots dwellers. Represented by the Director, Health of the Council, Habila Wakasso, the Head of Administration assured that the Council will ensure that the facility was put to effective use as well as maintain it on a regular basis. 